{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Apply tax and NI to household income for families with children under 11",
        "additional_details": "Single parents of children under 11 should also benefit from the same household tax rates.\r\n \r\nExample:\r\n \r\nFamily 1: only one person works and earns \u00a3120,000\r\n \r\nFamily 2: two people earn \u00a360,000\r\n \r\nFamily 1 receives approximately \u00a313,000 less after all tax and NI is taken.\r\n \r\nAlthough there is free childcare available, many families don\u2019t want to use childcare in early years and shouldn\u2019t be penalised for doing so.\r\n \r\nThe US and other countries apply a similar concept.\r\n \r\n",
        "background": "Make income tax and National Insurance apply at a household level (with tax allowances and tax band thresholds at twice the rate as for individuals) for families with children under 11.",
